member.name: ITfQueryEmbedded.QueryInsertEmbedded
member.summary: Determines if the active context can accept an embedded object.
member.param: A GUID that identifies the service associated with the object. This value can be NULL if pFormatEtc is valid.
Pointer to a structure that contains data about the object to be embedded. This value can be NULL if pguidService is valid.
Pointer to a Boolean value that receives the query result. This value receives a nonzero value if the object can be embedded, or zero otherwise.

returns.para: This method can return one of these values.

listheader.description: One or more parameters are invalid.

member.name: ITfQueryEmbedded
member.summary: The ITfQueryEmbedded interface is implemented by the TSF manager and used by a text service to determine if a context can accept an embedded object.
